      "id": 358299,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>3-Bromo-1-phenyl-1-propene shows a complex NMR spectrum in which the vinylic proton at C2 is coupled with both the C1 vinylic proton (<i>J</i> = 16 Hz) and the C3 methylene protons (<i>J</i> = 8 Hz). Draw a tree diagram for the C2 proton signal, and account for the fact that a five-line multiplet is observed.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa1lVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--3d4d63b1a8c547ad71d8cb7f5fb54ed0be3c5731/OChem_13_08_004.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of 3-Bromo-1-phenyl-1-propene with carbon atoms in the chain labeled.\">",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": [],
      "collaborator_solutions": [
        {
          "images": [],
          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "<p><i>J</i><sub>1–2</sub> = 16 Hz; <i>J</i><sub>2–3</sub> = 8 Hz</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa2NVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--99363b44044562ed282046f1bbfc6ff1d3864efb/OChem_13_EC_203.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of 3-Bromo-1-phenyl-1-propene and its proton splitting tree diagram that shows J 1-2 and J 2-3 values equals 16 and 8 Hertz, respectively.\">"
        }
      ],
